g + geom_point(aes(color = class))

Get me some shapes!

gap_wide <- readr::read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OHI-Science/data-science-training/master/data/gapminder_wide.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_double(),
##   continent = col_character(),
##   country = col_character(),
##   pop_2002 = col_integer(),
##   pop_2007 = col_integer()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
## use gather
#turn gap_wide into long format
gap_long <- gap_wide %>%
  gather(key = obstype_year,
         value = obs_values,
         dplyr::starts_with("pop"),
         dplyr::starts_with("lifeExp"),
         dplyr::starts_with("gdpPercap"))

## use separate 
gap_long <- gap_wide %>%
  gather(key = obstype_year,
         value = obs_values,
         -continent, -country) %>% 
  separate(obstype_year,
           into = c("obs_type", "year"),
           sep = "_",
           convert = TRUE)

Plot long form data

life_df <- gap_long %>% 
  filter(obs_type == "lifeExp", 
         continent == "Americas")

ggplot(life_df,aes(x= year, y = obs_values, color = country)) + 
  geom_line()

meanLE_df <- gap_long %>% 
  filter(obs_type == "lifeExp",
         year >= 1982,
         year <= 2007) %>% 
  group_by(continent, year) %>% 
  summarize(mean = mean(obs_values))

ggplot(meanLE_df,aes(x= year, y = mean, color = continent)) + 
  geom_line()

gap_normal <- gap_long %>% 
  spread(key = obs_type,
         value = obs_values)
